16:["$","p","11",{"children":[["$","strong","0",{"children":"MATH"}]," is how you figure stuff out — and plan for the future. Just like having different tools in a shed — a chisel, a hammer, a scraping blade — each equation solves a different problem. What is Math Good For? How about STAYING ALIVE?"]}]
17:["$","p","12",{"children":["All these people, across centuries and continents, have been grinding away at math problems — and you get to come along, la-tee-dah, and use any and all of their hard-earned equations —for free! Mind you - this was ",["$","strong","1",{"children":"not"}]," always the case."]}]
18:["$","p","13",{"children":["We've been gathering these magical spells, publishing them, teaching them, passing them on. It's",["$","strong","1",{"children":["$","em",null,{"children":" the universal human language of logic and reason "}]}],"— a model for understanding the world around us. And yet most of us never take the time to dig in and learn it."]}]
19:["$","p","14",{"children":["If you work for a living and you don't want to be poor in the future, you sure as hell need to start learning some math. Compound interest, baby. It's not as simple as it sounds — and yet it is magical and profound. If you're not familiar with the ",["$","strong","1",{"children":"compound interest equation"}],", then I implore you to spend some time learning about this little gem. Einstein called this equation man’s greatest invention. The sooner you learn it, the better your life will become."]}]
